summary: This code imports the os module, prints "enter normal shell", executes a bash shell using os.system(), and finally prints "exit normal shell". It provides access to a normal shell within the script's execution context.

details.comment: This code imports the os module, prints "enter normal shell", executes a bash shell using os.system(), and finally prints "exit normal shell". It provides access to a normal shell within the script's execution context.
details.content:
import os
print("enter normal shell")
os.system("bash")
print("exit normal shell")
